node.text:
You don’t have to be completely off grid to start homesteading NOW. Many of y’all are intimidated by the process, but I’m here to tell you-as someone that grew up in a trailer park in Florida, it’s easy-and fun.
-
Start with chickens, micro greens, jarring/canning veggies. The more you can learn and adapt in providing your own sustainable sustenance, the more self reliant you’ll be.
-
Let’s do this!
*I knew you dudes wouldn’t come here to watch me feed goats, so I used her to at least get ya started.

node.text:
PRESENCE PATROLS
Neighborhood Watch was started by the National Sheriffs Association in 1972. According to the Department of Justice it  reduces crime by 16% in Neighborhood Watch communities.
-
The reality is we care less about our neighbors and communities than ever before. We hold up in our homes with the doors locked and blinds shut.
-
In Special Operations I learned the benefit of presence patrols in and around the FireBases. You can’t identify potential threats by being locked down at home. Drive your local neighborhood, observe what’s in and out of patterns and report suspicious activity.
-
Do you have a Neighborhood Watch in your community?

node.text:
TF160
Was an honor hanging out with the PAO @reedknutson and the men of Task Force 160th.
-
I met an officer that returned after 8 years of stepping away as a pastor compelled to serve and fly again.
-
A CW4 that flies the Attack Helo that loves his job and is living a dream.
-
An MH6 pilot that’s looking at his transition with few options that compare to the epic career of the Regiment.
-
Ran into one of my younger CIF/CRF Assaulters that’s now flying for SOAR a decade later.
-
Heard stories of legends, real men, that have sacrificed it all and many stories of Valor of men still serving.
-
While the elected officials punch their clock, the brave men and women of the military and Special Operations get it done… so proud to call you brothers in arms and so proud of your service to this country. I’ll leave you with something I wrote as a young Sniper in the CIF, thinking about my life and my favorite platform the little bird.
-
NSDQ!
-
If I could choose to be reincarnated I would come back as a AH-6 little bird. Starting my life as a sight seeing tour guide so I can be connected to the people, I would learn peace, humility, and understanding. Once I built a reputation for the “compassionate one” I will have a mid life crisis. Boiling a rage of discontent and discourse I would have 6 guns strapped to my body and take out my frustration on all the evil ones I learned about in my touring days. I will have men that still believe in humanity use me to protect it. They will nick name me "Martyrdom Maker." At the end of it all, if all goes right I'll be preserved and put on display in the Airborne and Special Operations museum in Fayettteville, NC, with a plaque that reads…
“The Martrydom Maker, he came, he saw, he killed a lot of bad guys." Ah... If I was a little bird.
-

node.text:
Afghan Dreamin.
The Wild West.
-
General Miller advised against pulling all contingencies out of country.
-
I remember hearing the stories of how the Muj. strung wire from mountain to mountain and would take down Mi17 helos. Shoe string budgets with insurgent ingenuity took down a power house. 
-
My issues here are simple. The command I came from plans contingencies, you better believe we had a plan. The politicians thought they knew better… through ignorance and a lack of Leadership we ignored the men, the mission, and made a political decision forgetting every lesson we’ve ever learned.
-
I experienced this level of incompetence in Libya and abroad. Listening to the Secretary of State justify their decision on ABC, even as his own personnel are literally fighting for their security and lives-speaks to the air of arrogance and incompetence in this administration.
-
Our sons will be fighting and fixing the errors of our ignorance. 
-
#afghanistan #war #khan
